# Implementation Plan: Transform Mabel into Proactive Chief of Staff

**Based on:** `gleaming-fluttering-boot.md` (original plan), full codebase audit of `.clawdbot/` and `clawd/`

---

## Senior-Level Assessment

The original plan has the right vision but over-engineers the implementation. Three critical insights reshape the approach:

1. **The clawdbot cron system sends text prompts to Mabel, not scripts.** Every cron job is a `systemEvent` text payload that Mabel interprets using her existing tools (Gmail, Calendar, Notion, WhatsApp, filesystem). The plan's proposed Node.js scripts (`autonomous-heartbeat.js`, `daily-digest.js`, etc.) should be **cron job entries with text payloads**, not code.

2. **79% of client data is empty.** Only 19 of 92 records have contact info. Building pipeline automation, email templates, and knowledge graph entities on top of empty data creates complexity with zero payoff. Fix the data first.

3. **Notion is the task system.** Brad explicitly chose Notion over GoHighLevel on Jan 26. The Mabel Project Board is operational with 53+ items. A local `tasks.json` would create a competing source of truth.

---

## What to Change (and What NOT to Change)

### Files to MODIFY

| File | What to Do |
|------|-----------|
| `clawd\IDENTITY.md` | Add proactive Chief of Staff posture (keep it short, ~20 lines total) |
| `clawd\SOUL.md` | Add "Proactive vs Reactive" and "Approval Gate Philosophy" sections at end |
| `clawd\USER.md` | Add Kolbe deep-dive and communication preferences sections |
| `clawd\HEARTBEAT.md` | Expand from 12 lines to ~40 lines with client pipeline checks, email monitoring, and content inventory checks |
| `clawd\TOOLS.md` | Remove GoHighLevel section (ditched Jan 26), add "No CRM" note |
| `clawd\AGENTS.md` | Add "Autonomous Operations" section after the Heartbeats section (proactive vs interactive modes, approval gate pattern) |
| `clawd\memory\heartbeat-state.json` | Extend with: `lastMorningBriefing`, `lastFollowUpDigest`, `lastEmailScan`, `lastEveningRecap`, `lastClientReview`, `lastNotionSync` |
| `clawd\data\CLIENT_DB_README.md` | Add pipeline stage definitions, sparse overlay documentation |
| `.clawdbot\cron\jobs.json` | Add 5 new cron jobs (see below) |

### Files to CREATE

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `clawd\data\client-activity.json` | Sparse overlay for pipeline/contact/review data (only clients with actual data, keyed by client ID) |
| `clawd\PROACTIVE.md` | Autonomous operations manual (what to monitor, when to act, approval gates, digest formats) |

### Files to NOT Create (deferred or unnecessary)

| Proposed File | Why Not |
|---------------|---------|
| `data\tasks.json` | Notion Project Board is the task system. No parallel local file. |
| `data\mabel-state.json` | Extend `heartbeat-state.json` instead. One state file, one source of truth. |
| `config\pipeline-stages.json` | Over-engineering. Document stages in CLIENT_DB_README.md, check via heartbeat instructions. |
| `config\cron-jobs.json` | Cron jobs live in `.clawdbot\cron\jobs.json` (platform-managed). No separate config needed. |
| `config\email-templates\*.md` | Premature. No email send capability with approval workflow exists yet. Build 2-3 templates after the follow-up digest is running. |
| `scripts\autonomous-heartbeat.js` | The heartbeat IS the autonomous loop. Update HEARTBEAT.md instructions instead. |
| `scripts\daily-digest.js` through `scripts\evening-recap.js` | These should be cron job text payloads in jobs.json, not JS scripts. |
| `life\areas\clients\*` (92 entities) | Massive scope creep. Let the existing fact extraction promote clients to entities organically (only when 3+ meaningful interactions exist). |

